1. Which PowerShell profile has the lowest precedence?
current user, current host

2. Which PowerShell profile has the highest precedence?
all users, all hosts

3. Which PowerShell variable stores the current userâ€™s home directory?
$home

4. Which PowerShell variable stores the installation directory for PowerShell?
$PSHome

5. Which PowerShell variable stores the path to the "Current User, Current Host" profile?
$profile

6. What command would you run to view the help for PowerShell Profiles?
get-help about_profiles

7. What command would tell you if there was a profile loaded for All Users All Hosts?
test-path -path $profile.allusersallhosts
